Bound in iron and with a heavy lock, this heavy chest was obviously meant to protect something of value.
[This is a 15 foot length of rope, a grappling hook attached to its end.  You may be able to find some use for it during your travels...]
Used in times of trouble, these priestly waters comfort the sorrowful and make great men of lowly cowards.
This tonic is sovereign against venoms, mineral toxins, diseases, and poisons of all sorts.
This thick concoction smells dark and musty, like a forest after heavy rains.
Called "portable priests" by more cynical adventurers, these holy infusions are of great use to the average adventurer.
These blood-red infusions, made from the horns and heart of young bulls, grant the drinker great physical strength.
This sparkling potion greatly increases the drinker's Dexterity.
Made of hot liquid poured over scorched and pungent beans, this strong-smelling brew did not get its name from its appearance. It helps clear and fortify the mind against spells that affect the mind.
With the power to return people from the very brink of death, these potions do not come cheaply.
Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Abaran.
These curative potions are too expensive for most civilians, and are used almost exclusively by soldiers and adventurers.
With the power to staunch the flow of blood or knit a broken bone, these potions are in common use among the dangerous professions.
With their ability to smooth the complexion, gloss the hair, and brighten the eyes, these potions find regular use among the nobility. But it shall make anyone more comely.
A potion of endurance combines various magical components to increase stamina and overall health, though it does not heal damage.
These potions are eagerly sought by sages, scholars, and adventuring wizards alike. When imbibed, they grant a bonus to the drinker's Intelligence score.
These potions are in equal demand by adventurers and scholars, allowing for the imbiber to clear their thoughts in the pursuit of remembering vague legends and tales of old.
This milky red potion seems to open the drinker's perception of his environment, making him at once more observant and more resistant to effects that target the mind.
This suit has been finely woven to suit the tastes of upper nobility.

This pack contains enough food and water for a single day of adventuring. Most nobles and merchants use this sort of food pack while traveling out in the wilds of the empire. Though there are many other substitutes for traditional packed rations, this is the most popular choice of those that can afford it.

This item can be used as a ration. You will need to have some form of ration in your inventory to gain any benefit from resting.
